Kakamega chiefs and assistant chiefs have been urged to acquaint themselves with new technologies. The recently formed Kakamega County Chiefs’ Welfare Group yesterday told members to enroll for short courses to improve services to residents. “Most of us need to be at the same level with the rest of the world. That’s why, through this group, we urge our members to upscale their knowledge,” secretary general Walter Mukungu said. Mukungu  the senior chief for Kisa East location in Khwisero  said the world is fast-changing through technology, especially the internet. New internet-related crimes emerge and chief should keep abreast of the changes, he said.